<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 02:07:14 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>斯坦福 CS231N 计算机视觉深度学习 I 2025</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/stanford-cs231n-deep-learning-for-computer-vision-i-2025</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 02:07:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/stanford-cs231n-deep-learning-for-computer-vision-i-2025</guid></item><item><title>无电池皮肤适形可穿戴系统可测量心电图信号</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/battery-free-skin-conformal-wearable-system-can-measure-electrocardiogram-signals</link><description>首尔国立大学 (SNU) 电气与计算机工程系 Jerald Yoo 教授领导的研究小组开发了一种皮肤适形可穿戴医疗保健系统“SkinECG”，无需电池即可测量心电图 (ECG) 信号。通过将能量收集与人体耦合电力传输相结合，该研究为可穿戴设备中最关键的挑战之一：电源提供了一种新的解决方案。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/battery-free-skin-conformal-wearable-system-can-measure-electrocardiogram-signals2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 01:52:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/battery-free-skin-conformal-wearable-system-can-measure-electrocardiogram-signals</guid></item><item><title>雅各布·巴兰德斯——“量子理论的新表述”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/jacob-barandes-a-new-formulation-of-quantum-theory</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 01:37:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/jacob-barandes-a-new-formulation-of-quantum-theory</guid></item><item><title>小型研究表明一次性细胞疗法可以控制艾滋病毒感染</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/small-study-shows-one-time-cell-therapy-can-control-hiv-infection</link><description>与之前的艾滋病毒“治疗”不同，癌症患者接受来自具有罕见基因突变的捐赠者的骨髓干细胞，可以抵抗艾滋病毒感染，研究人员表示，CAR-T可以被更广泛的患者群体使用。第一阶段试验涉及 CAR-T，这是一种一次性疗法，患者的 T 细胞在实验室中被提取、改变和繁殖，然后输回体内。在这种情况下，CAR-T 靶向 HIV 的 CD4 和 CCR5 结合位点。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/small-study-shows-one-time-cell-therapy-can-control-hiv-infection.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 01:22:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/small-study-shows-one-time-cell-therapy-can-control-hiv-infection</guid></item><item><title>Nintendo 64 模拟器刚刚为整个库实现了回滚网络代码：“老实说，这并不难”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/nintendo-64-emulator-just-implemented-rollback-netcode-for-the-entire-library-it-was-honestly-not-that-hard</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 01:07:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/nintendo-64-emulator-just-implemented-rollback-netcode-for-the-entire-library-it-was-honestly-not-that-hard</guid></item><item><title>为未来的火星任务设计原位发电站</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/designing-in-situ-power-stations-for-future-mars-missions</link><description>您正在实验室中分析舒适的火星栖息地内的火星风化层样本，执行第五次人类火星任务。得益于 MARS-MES（火星大气资源和多模式能源系统），栖息地内的电力一直在完美流动，包括一般栖息地照明、科学实验室、睡眠区、运动设备、船员用于休息和放松的虚拟现实耳机、氧气和燃料生成以及水。所有这一切都来自将火星大气转化为可用的电力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/designing-in-situ-power-stations-for-future-mars-missions.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 00:52:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/designing-in-situ-power-stations-for-future-mars-missions</guid></item><item><title>日常设备如何更快地训练人工智能，同时将个人数据保留在设备上</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-everyday-devices-could-train-ai-faster-while-keeping-personal-data-on-device</link><description>麻省理工学院研究人员开发的一种新方法可以将保护隐私的人工智能训练方法加速约 81%。这一进步可以让更多资源受限的边缘设备（例如传感器和智能手表）部署更准确的人工智能模型，同时保证用户数据的安全。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-everyday-devices-could-train-ai-faster-while-keeping-personal-data-on-device.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 00:37:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-everyday-devices-could-train-ai-faster-while-keeping-personal-data-on-device</guid></item><item><title>人工智能如何寻找副作用更少的癌症治疗方法英国广播公司新闻</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-ai-is-finding-cancer-treatments-with-fewer-side-effects-bbc-news</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 14:52:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-ai-is-finding-cancer-treatments-with-fewer-side-effects-bbc-news</guid></item><item><title>人工智能预测癌症转移风险</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-predicts-risk-of-cancer-metastases</link><description>UNIGE 科学家开发了一种人工智能算法，能够预测癌症转移和复发的风险。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-predicts-risk-of-cancer-metastases2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 14:37:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-predicts-risk-of-cancer-metastases</guid></item><item><title>固体中核自旋的实验量子核技巧</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/experimental-quantum-kernel-trick-with-nuclear-spins-in-a-solid</link><description>楠本 T.、御手洗 K.、藤井 K. &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/experimental-quantum-kernel-trick-with-nuclear-spins-in-a-solid.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 14:22:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/experimental-quantum-kernel-trick-with-nuclear-spins-in-a-solid</guid></item></channel></rss>